1
00:00:03,520 --> 00:00:06,720
Trust me, it tastes completely different
when you grill it. Totally.

2
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:09,880
Yeah, you already told me that.
At six in the morning, when you woke me up,

3
00:00:09,960 --> 00:00:12,440
which is three hours early. And a half.

4
00:00:12,520 --> 00:00:14,520
Fine. You'll thank me for waking you up earlier.

5
00:00:15,040 --> 00:00:17,040
You have no idea how fast the good spots get taken.

6
00:00:17,120 --> 00:00:19,480
What's the big deal? It's a picnic.
Does it really matter where we sit?

7
00:00:19,560 --> 00:00:21,160
What’s that? The girls will hear more.

8
00:00:22,120 --> 00:00:25,480
Mom didn’t mean to say it like that.
It’s really, really important where we sit. Very.

9
00:00:25,560 --> 00:00:27,800
Yeah.
-We’ll have the picnic

10
00:00:27,880 --> 00:00:29,080
at the usual Rosen family spot,

11
00:00:29,160 --> 00:00:32,439
which is the perfect place for a perfect picnic.
-Oh, honey, I don’t want to tell you

12
00:00:32,520 --> 00:00:36,240
but the success of the picnic doesn’t depend
on where we sit, but who we sit with.

13
00:00:36,320 --> 00:00:37,920
In your case, that’s already a lost cause
because it’s with your family.

14
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:40,520
Okay, so I know it sounds weird
coming from me,

15
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:44,040
I’m a realist, but there are places
that have good energy.

16
00:00:44,120 --> 00:00:47,600
Yeah. Where? In his bed?
-Also. And in the forest.

17
00:00:48,680 --> 00:00:51,880
Every time we got to that specific spot
the fights would stop,

18
00:00:52,240 --> 00:00:55,000
the exams would pause, and as strange as it sounds,

19
00:00:55,080 --> 00:00:57,720
my family really functioned like a family.

20
00:00:57,800 --> 00:01:00,160
Your family functioned like a family? That really sounds weird.

21
00:01:00,240 --> 00:01:02,360
Alright, enough, sit down, really.
Don’t mess with my tradition.

22
00:01:03,040 --> 00:01:05,680
I spent all my childhood picnicking
in the same spot, under those same trees,

23
00:01:06,240 --> 00:01:07,880
and all my adulthood I’ll picnic in that same spot,

24
00:01:07,960 --> 00:01:10,120
and when your daughters grow up and want to picnic,

25
00:01:10,200 --> 00:01:13,960
they’ll know exactly where they want
to be pampered. With them.

26
00:01:14,960 --> 00:01:18,680
Come on, let’s sing. "In the forest, in the forest, in the forest"...

27
00:01:18,760 --> 00:01:19,960
Volanshnu, lanashnuyo

28
00:01:20,040 --> 00:01:21,640
Enough. It’s Saturday morning. Come on.

29
00:01:27,240 --> 00:01:29,920
Look at me, look at me and...

30
00:01:39,280 --> 00:01:41,800
Okay girls, you remember
what you’re looking for, right?

31
00:01:41,880 --> 00:01:46,320
A big tree with a heart carved on it,
yes, and inside it says "Shai"

32
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:49,120
and another name that starts with an Aleph. Got it?

33
00:01:49,680 --> 00:01:50,600
So let’s go.

34
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:56,760
Come on. Can’t we do this here?
-You’re so funny.

35
00:01:56,840 --> 00:01:59,760
I don’t think we’re heading in the right direction.

36
00:01:59,840 --> 00:02:01,440
"I’ll go out to the forest..."

37
00:02:01,520 --> 00:02:05,760
Want to do a cannon?
-No. No. Speaking of "I’ll go out to the forest",

38
00:02:05,840 --> 00:02:07,600
who’s that cute girl?

39
00:02:08,360 --> 00:02:09,320
Who?
-The curls.

40
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:11,920
When are you going to tell me what that Aleph is about?
-What Aleph?

41
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:16,000
The Aleph you carved next to your name,
that you had a heart that said "Shai",

42
00:02:16,560 --> 00:02:19,240
what you told the girls not to tell me.
-How did I know I couldn’t trust them?

43
00:02:19,320 --> 00:02:21,680
Worth it?
-Enough, sit down. Do me a favor, drop it,

44
00:02:21,760 --> 00:02:23,760
that was ages ago.
-Yeah, of course it was ages ago.

45
00:02:25,080 --> 00:02:26,080
Slim?
-No.

46
00:02:26,160 --> 00:02:27,920
Are you ready to let me
focus on finding this place?

47
00:02:29,560 --> 00:02:30,920
Blonde or blonde?

48
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:34,360
Enough, sit down, trust me that when we get to the specific place

49
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:35,960
even your questions will disappear.

50
00:02:36,040 --> 00:02:38,400
Seriously.
-Peace and calm.

51
00:02:39,880 --> 00:02:41,840
Do we need to go through passport control?

52
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:47,240
Adam, explain to her that this forest
is planted within the State of Israel.

53
00:02:47,320 --> 00:02:51,280
She only knows Tel Aviv.
North of the Yarkon is Ramat Aviv

54
00:02:51,360 --> 00:02:54,240
and the Golan Heights.
To her, they can give it back to the Syrians.

55
00:02:54,320 --> 00:02:56,400
East of the Ayalon is the Palestinian state,

56
00:02:56,480 --> 00:02:58,440
south of Abulafia, in Jaffa, that’s Egypt.

57
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:03,360
Not only is she left-wing, Pinchas,
she’s extra, extra left.

58
00:03:03,920 --> 00:03:05,560
And do you know how hard it is to find in my size?

59
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:11,400
In a second, Dad will crack and tell you.
Was her name Eti?

60
00:03:11,480 --> 00:03:14,080
No, and why aren’t you looking?
-Orit?

61
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:17,640
Mom, this game isn't fun.
-Okay, just a sec, he's counting to ten.

62
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:21,040
Olga?
-I'm pretty sure it was here.

63
00:03:21,960 --> 00:03:23,520
If you guys were looking, it would happen faster.

64
00:03:24,280 --> 00:03:25,120
I can't believe it's gone.

65
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:27,920
Maybe there was a fire here.

66
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:31,000
Come on, babe, enough. Maybe we should stay here? Come on.
-How's the vibe here?

67
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:32,680
You're wasting your time, I'm on fire with energy,

68
00:03:32,760 --> 00:03:35,000
my chakras are wide open. It's unreal.

69
00:03:35,080 --> 00:03:37,240
Based on your sarcasm, I get it wasn't here.

70
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:40,000
Wait, here it is.
-What, are you sure?

71
00:03:40,080 --> 00:03:41,920
No.
-Shai.

72
00:03:43,040 --> 00:03:44,360
Maybe it was on that hill over there.

73
00:03:44,440 --> 00:03:47,920
Babe, listen, listen,
it doesn't matter where the picnic is.

74
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,880
I promise you, you'll have an amazing picnic,

75
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:51,920
magical, just like your childhood memories.

76
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:55,080
You'll enjoy it with your family,
you'll enjoy it with their family.

77
00:03:55,160 --> 00:03:58,080
Just without Ivga.
-Her name wasn't Ivga,

78
00:03:58,760 --> 00:04:00,520
and according to your divisions, it wasn't here either.

79
00:04:01,760 --> 00:04:05,320
I wonder if Itamar knew where it was.
Come on, let's go, to the hill.

80
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:06,480
Alexis?
-No.

81
00:04:07,440 --> 00:04:08,920
Orchid?
-Come on!

82
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:11,000
Addis Ababa?
-Sit down.

83
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:12,360
Angelina.

84
00:04:12,440 --> 00:04:14,640
Because, because, how did we know?

85
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:16,200
Acne!

86
00:04:16,880 --> 00:04:19,880
Babe, watch out on the turn.
-I don't get how you could stay quiet about this.

87
00:04:19,959 --> 00:04:21,600
I didn't stay quiet. You saw I yelled at him.

88
00:04:21,680 --> 00:04:23,800
You laughed, Itamar.
-But loudly.

89
00:04:23,880 --> 00:04:27,000
Your son put a dead animal in my pita, Itamar,
a dead animal!

90
00:04:27,080 --> 00:04:29,440
A sausage. Do you want me to cry?

91
00:04:29,520 --> 00:04:31,520
A dead animal. You know how I
feel about that, right?

92
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:34,640
Okay, enough already, babe, alright? He apologized.
That's enough and... you caught it in time.

93
00:04:35,080 --> 00:04:36,880
It's not like he killed the animal just for them.

94
00:04:37,200 --> 00:04:39,640
It had been dead for a long time
in our fridge, babe.

95
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:42,160
Babe, babe, babe, it's slipping away fast.

96
00:04:43,520 --> 00:04:44,920
Son, are you feeling okay here?

97
00:04:45,480 --> 00:04:46,960
I think so.
-You think?

98
00:04:47,320 --> 00:04:48,160
Whatever, son.

99
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:51,480
Great, so whatever, everyone feels
good or thinks they feel good.

100
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:53,640
Can we start eating already?

101
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,200
Yoohoo...

102
00:04:59,280 --> 00:05:02,080
Wow, Alibo,
for a brief moment there was really good energy here.

103
00:05:02,160 --> 00:05:05,360
Yoohoo...
-Yoohoo T! Yoohoo.

104
00:05:05,440 --> 00:05:06,560
-Shabbat Shalom.

105
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:08,560
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

106
00:05:10,240 --> 00:05:11,760
Sh, very crowded.

107
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:16,000
I think you came in the wrong shoes.

108
00:05:16,080 --> 00:05:18,080
So fix it, fix it.
-Adam, take off your stuff. Sit down.

109
00:05:18,960 --> 00:05:19,800
Here?

110
00:05:20,960 --> 00:05:22,760
Come on, I'll pack it up. Come on, we're moving.

111
00:05:23,640 --> 00:05:25,320
He put the sausage in my face.

112
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:28,960
Okay, we got it.
The sausage, the sausage, the sausage, the sausage.

113
00:05:29,040 --> 00:05:31,560
So maybe it's really time for you to stop
with that stupid pose of yours

114
00:05:31,640 --> 00:05:33,120
and start eating like a normal person.

115
00:05:36,240 --> 00:05:39,280
Okay, sorry. I apologize, babe,
I went a bit overboard. I'm sorry.

116
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:43,360
I knew it. No. I knew it.
That's why you didn't get mad at him, because you agree with him.

117
00:05:43,440 --> 00:05:44,760
I'm not...
-I'm not talking to you.

118
00:05:48,360 --> 00:05:51,240
I don't get what was wrong with that place.
-What is it, is Itamar there?

119
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:55,280
What, is he coming with Michal's whole family?
-Are you crazy?

120
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:56,440
So no.

121
00:05:57,000 --> 00:06:00,760
I hope they don't settle down too close,
so we won't have to move.

122
00:06:00,840 --> 00:06:03,120
No, they're going over there.
-Oh, thank God.

123
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:05,160
Can we start grilling?

124
00:06:09,960 --> 00:06:12,640
Sho
9% and
and, yayom
a

125
00:06:12,720 --> 00:06:15,280
Come help Dad light the fire, please.

126
00:06:15,360 --> 00:06:18,600
I've been doing this alone for forty years, Riki.
I can manage by myself.

127
00:06:18,680 --> 00:06:21,480
What do you care if he comes to help you
light the fire?

128
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:23,680
Nonsense. It's fine. Dad, is there fire?

129
00:06:23,760 --> 00:06:27,720
Riki, did you pack a lighter?
-Yeah, but where is it now?

130
00:06:28,280 --> 00:06:30,160
You brought the whole house, just not fire?

131
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:33,200
You've been doing this alone for forty years, right?

132
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:37,520
Since when do I pack anything at home?
-Oh, great. Whine about it.

133
00:06:38,160 --> 00:06:40,920
I told you there are no good vibes here?
-Oh, look what I found.

134
00:06:41,240 --> 00:06:45,920
Maybe we can find some good vibes in this.
Look how nice. Toh, toh, toh.

135
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:47,080
Ah, here's some good energy.

136
00:06:47,680 --> 00:06:52,360
Shai, maybe you should go ask our neighbors for fire?
They seem nice to me.

137
00:06:52,440 --> 00:06:56,800
Nice? You didn't want them sitting next to us.
-And they didn't sit next to us.

138
00:06:56,880 --> 00:07:00,280
Which makes them very nice in my eyes.
-Okay.

139
00:07:05,280 --> 00:07:08,040
I'm glad you came. I was really worried.

140
00:07:08,880 --> 00:07:12,360
Hello, hey.
-You're late. Did Michal drive?

141
00:07:13,960 --> 00:07:15,920
What, babe? Everything okay?
-I don't know.

142
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:19,360
We're just going to the bathroom for a sec.
-I need to go too.

143
00:07:19,440 --> 00:07:21,320
Me too, me too.
-Come on.

144
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:25,080
Enough, Mom, we're not moving.

145
00:07:25,160 --> 00:07:26,840
Look at the time. Here.

146
00:07:27,680 --> 00:07:28,840
Hello.

147
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:29,920
Shabbat Shalom.

148
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:33,720
Shabbat Shalom. Am I interrupting?
-Not at all. Go ahead.

149
00:07:34,960 --> 00:07:38,680
I feel awkward, even a bit silly,
but do you happen to have fire?

150
00:07:41,320 --> 00:07:44,040
Fire?
-Yeah, my mom...

151
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:47,080
Forget it, you won't understand.
-You'd be surprised.

152
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:50,680
There's fire. Yes.
-Is there fire?

153
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:56,840
Do you want those lighters too?
-No, no. Just fire. Fire.

154
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:01,440
Want something to eat?

155
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:03,040
<i>Ar...</i>

156
00:08:03,120 --> 00:08:05,880
Small.
-Wow, my mom will kill me.

157
00:08:07,960 --> 00:08:10,240
You know what, why not?
-Mom, get him a pita.

158
00:08:10,320 --> 00:08:11,920
Maybe one pita. No...

159
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:15,160
Come on, babe. Take it. Here, smoke over there.

160
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:16,840
We're waiting for you.
-Okay.

161
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:22,080
Come on, what's up?
-Raz let me eat meat,

162
00:08:22,160 --> 00:08:24,400
and Itamar didn't even yell at him.
-Wow.

163
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:25,840
And that's not even the point. I'm not his mom

164
00:08:25,920 --> 00:08:27,760
and I know I'm not his mom
because if I were his mom,

165
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:30,160
he'd be spoiled, maybe even short, like Yanir Bari.

166
00:08:30,240 --> 00:08:33,000
No, he has a smell from his shoes that you hate,
and I tell him, Raz,

167
00:08:33,080 --> 00:08:36,280
there are so many creams and products today.
There are halablubim, there are za'atar seeds...

168
00:08:36,360 --> 00:08:38,919
Okay, okay, Michal, let's move on, yeah...
-Alright, sorry. Never mind,

169
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:40,919
but every time there's an issue,
Itamar is right there by his side.

170
00:08:41,480 --> 00:08:44,039
What do you want? He's his son.
-And I don't hate him.

171
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:45,640
Who?
-Raz, who else.

172
00:08:46,280 --> 00:08:48,920
Every time he's not around
everything's fine between me and Itamar.

173
00:08:49,440 --> 00:08:51,840
I have no problem with the little one. Anyway
I don't understand a word she says,

174
00:08:51,920 --> 00:08:55,800
but the older one... I'm telling you,
I wish he would just disappear.

175
00:08:57,400 --> 00:09:00,600
So what? Rosh Hashanah is just around the corner, huh?

176
00:09:01,600 --> 00:09:05,640
What corner?
-She's not the brightest highlighter in the pencil case. What?

177
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:07,560
What pencil case? What is he talking about?

178
00:09:07,640 --> 00:09:11,920
Oh, there you are. How long did that take?
What is this? Did they feed you?

179
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:14,800
It was great.
-What was it, schnitzel?

180
00:09:14,880 --> 00:09:16,920
No, Mom, they're not the kind of people who make schnitzels.

181
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:19,160
Ah, Yemenites.
-Arabs, yeah.

182
00:09:19,240 --> 00:09:21,280
Let’s move on from here.
-Come on, Mom, really. Let’s go, enough.

183
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:24,360
Arabs from Jaffa, totally Israeli.
-No, you’re right.

184
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:26,840
If we move now, they’ll feel it’s because of them.

185
00:09:26,920 --> 00:09:28,840
You never know how they’ll react.

186
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:32,840
Thanks. Go ahead.

187
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:37,440
It’s not fair. You’d expect that after a few weeks

188
00:09:37,520 --> 00:09:39,120
this family would already know me.

189
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:43,200
I don’t know, maybe you should stop
punishing Raz once and for all.

190
00:09:43,640 --> 00:09:45,160
What do you mean?
-Punish him.

191
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:48,200
Like not letting him play his stupid video games
at your place.

192
00:09:48,760 --> 00:09:51,240
You think Itamar will let me?
-What, he won’t let you punish him?

193
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:54,120
No, he won’t care. He’ll even be happy.
-So?

194
00:09:54,440 --> 00:09:57,200
He won’t let me take his video game
because then Itamar will have to talk to him

195
00:09:57,280 --> 00:09:58,720
and keep him busy, and that’s already punishing Itamar.

196
00:10:00,560 --> 00:10:04,200
Come on, what’s up, girls?
They must have drunk a lot on the way, you have no idea.

197
00:10:04,760 --> 00:10:06,560
I want some too.
-Come on, go with the flow.

198
00:10:09,800 --> 00:10:12,640
Wait with the gas, Dad.
Give me that, give me that.

199
00:10:16,920 --> 00:10:18,280
At least let me light a match.

200
00:10:18,360 --> 00:10:20,360
We need twigs.
-What twigs? We need gasoline.

201
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:22,240
We need ones like these... come on...

202
00:10:23,480 --> 00:10:26,080
Light ones like these.
-Let’s just use newspapers, enough.

203
00:10:26,160 --> 00:10:28,120
We want to read them.
-The culture supplement?

204
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:29,840
Like anyone cares what’s written there anyway.

205
00:10:29,920 --> 00:10:33,320
Itamar, newspapers are dangerous.
The wind will come and there’ll be a fire...

206
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:35,000
Maybe we can siphon gas from one of the cars?

207
00:10:36,160 --> 00:10:37,640
They used to light ones like these over there.

208
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:40,440
Come on, so why didn’t you take?
-I thought we’d manage.

209
00:10:40,520 --> 00:10:42,760
You’re not going back there, okay?
-What’s your problem?

210
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:45,920
I’m tired of your nonsense.
I’m going to get lights like those.

211
00:10:46,400 --> 00:10:48,280
You see? If we were in the right place, this wouldn’t happen.

212
00:10:48,360 --> 00:10:50,680
What are you talking about? It was here.
-Not at all.

213
00:10:50,760 --> 00:10:54,520
I remember that table and those flies.

214
00:10:54,840 --> 00:10:56,320
I don’t remember it being this hot.

215
00:10:58,080 --> 00:10:59,080
Look, look.

216
00:11:00,840 --> 00:11:02,160
Just because they come and go,

217
00:11:02,240 --> 00:11:03,400
doesn’t mean they’re not okay, Mom.

218
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:09,520
Hey.
-Hi, hi.

219
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:13,800
Listen, I’m the brother of the... that guy who...

220
00:11:14,200 --> 00:11:16,320
The bald one.

221
00:11:16,400 --> 00:11:18,360
Yeah. Just me, I got my mom’s genes.

222
00:11:20,280 --> 00:11:22,960
I hope just in terms of hair, but... forget it.

223
00:11:23,040 --> 00:11:25,400
You wouldn’t understand.
-You’d be surprised.

